
  == ZClassic ==
 
Available commands:
zcash-cli            - Zcash commandline client

zcl-send TO_ADDR AMOUNT           - Sends ZCLs (only t-addr)
zcl-send FROM_ADDR TO_ADDR AMOUNT - Sends ZCLs (t-addr & z-addr support)

zcl-status           - ZClassic status. Note: After first run you should wait for downloading all current blocks
zcl-balance          - Total balance
zcl-listaddrs        - Lists wallet addresses
zcl-transactions     - Lists transactions
zcl-transaction TXID - Gets single transaction status
zcl-newaddr          - Gets new t-addr (public)
zcl-newzaddr         - Gets new z-addr (anonymous)
zcl-backup           - Backups wallet to 7zip password protected file
zcl-showwallet       - Prints wallet in console
zcl-connections      - Gets active connections
zcl-operations       - Latest operations statuses
zcl-config           - Prints zclassic.config to console
zcl-archive          - Archive zclassic blocks and chainstate
zcl-logs             - Prints ZClassic logs
zcl-stop             - Stop ZClassic daemon
exit                 - Stop ZClassic daemon and exit wallet

Import wallet: zcash-cli z_importwallet FILE

!!! Backup your wallet !!! - use 'zcl-exportwallet' command and copy file to secure location
